    "Misalignment of tomograms produced by serial sectioning can distort the reconstructed form of the imaged fossil's anatomy, meaning that its reliability in terms of honoring specimen geometry may be questionable in many cases (Costantini et al. 2015).",
    "Many-although not all-studies applying DL within paleontology are based on microfossils, which are less familiar than the fossils of larger organisms.",
    "Microfossils are the microscopic, fossilized remains of various organisms, including protists (eukaryotes that are not an animal, plant, or fungus), small animals, and small elements derived from a larger organism.",
    "As such, they do not represent a single group of organisms, but are drawn from across the tree of life.",
    "They are valuable tools in paleontology and geology due to their abundance and their ability to provide insights into ancient environments and evolutionary processes (Javaux and Benzerara 2009; Dalton 2002)."
  ],
